  <span id="freeText6825140824114239632" style="display:none">The finalist for the 1980 Pulitzer Prize for Fiction Birdy by William Wharton <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://www.pulitzer.org/prize-winners-by-category/219">https://www.pulitzer.org/prize-winner...</a><br />Nine out of 10<br /><br /><br />‘I am Spartacus’ is the famous line from the motion picture directed by Stanley Kubrick, screenplay written by Donald Trumbo (we find in the film Trumbo that Kirk Douglas went against conservative Hollywood, people like John Wayne, to give the task to the brilliant writer), starring the crème de la crème…I was thinking about it when reading through this book, for “I am Birdy’…I have two macaws (in size and screaming the equivalent of more canaries than the hero has and then some), mental issues (if you ask the spouse, I should be kept in a specialized institution…but then she might not be such a reliable source…unlike the vicious mother of the main character of the novel (who is as mean as you can find, the Ultimate Shrew) the consort is the one that brought one of the Big Fat Birds home, only she now attributes the move to yours truly, exclusively, since he is the one who sent pictures, saying that the red and green was so beautiful and thus she had to go and take him…otherwise, she never did anything I said, never mind to take up a suggestion and turn it into a real Winged Dragon on the premises…<br /><br />Only a few days ago I have read a short story, Tesla and Wife, included in another magnum opus nominated for the Pulitzer Prize, Love in Infant Monkeys by Lydia Millet <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://realini.blogspot.com/2021/08/from-collection-of-short-stories.html">http://realini.blogspot.com/2021/08/f...</a> from which we learnt that Tesla has had a passion for pigeons, just like Birdy, though the latter would become infatuated (perhaps we should say obsessed with canaries and flying…he thinks he can learn to speak the language of birds and more importantly, to fly like them) with the canary birds he breeds in his bedroom, until he gets permission to build an aviary near the garage, where he says he will have a business, making about $ 750 a year, an impressive sum in those days, when his father had, like most others, very low wages – we also have to consider inflation – Tesla said that he loved one dove in particular more than anything else…<br />Another book with a boy and a bird at the center that has come to mind is A Kestrel for a Knave by Barry Hines <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://realini.blogspot.com/2019/06/a-kestrel-for-knave-by-barry-hines-97.html">http://realini.blogspot.com/2019/06/a...</a>, with the important difference that A Kestrel is a predator, eating other birds, not singing to them…the similarities are many, for the dynamic in both books is rather sad, tragic at times, relationships within families are often hostile…in Birdy, Alfonso, Birdy’s best friend and almost an alter ego, the one who narrates perhaps half the story, for we have alternating chapters, in which both Birdy and his good friend tell us what has happened – or is happening as we move along- Alfonso is beaten mercilessly by his father. Until his mother, who speaks some sort of Sicilian dialect with her husband, which Al can understand, says ‘VIITORIO, BASTA’<br /><br />Birdy does not get mad generally, but Mr. Columbato does infuriate him, for at one point he sells a car on which Al and his friend had worked a lot to a member of the mob…an uncle is connected with the gangsters and one pays one hundred dollars for the eight cylinders vehicle, which had been brought to a splendid form by the two boys working together, only to find their efforts will have been in vain…<br /><br />Birdy is so aggravated that he walks to Mr. Columbato, against the warning of his friend, who has said that his father will kill him and he tries to explain to the impulsive, brutish fellow that they have a receipt for the car (which they do not) and he can call the police and it is better to have the name of the man who bought the car and explain, to avoid any trouble…’he will put you in a cement shirt and then you will be at the bottom of a river’ responds Vittorio Columbato, who is pushing the boy with his fingers, and he is such a strong man that there will be bruises left there…nonetheless, Birdy is known for his extraordinary abilities in fights and his superhuman resilience…when he met Al for the first time, the latter had tried hard to punch, but the hero has magic powers…he would fight a champion in wrestling and managed to beat the specialist, because he can escape from anything…when he fell from a reservoir, he survived miraculously…<br />Birdy’s mother may remind one reader of stories by the Pulitzer Prize Winner Robert Olen Butler <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://realini.blogspot.com/2016/09/open-arms-and-mr-green-by-robert-olen.html">http://realini.blogspot.com/2016/09/o...</a> stories in which birds suffer, are eaten…The mother of the main personage is very offensive, she is against him raising any creatures, when he had pigeons she did all she could to get rid of them – at one point, when he is in hospital, after the major fall from a reservoir where he was trying to get more birds, she poisons the two most beautiful pigeons that have homed near the house, albeit the boy does not know and Alfonso does not tell him – and he lives in constant terror of what his mother would do to his poor creatures…<br /><br />He is so scared that he buys some pine perfume solution to make the room smell better, because the woman is always complaining and threatening, after he has one female bird, named Birdie, not Birdy, he buys a male with wonderful flying abilities, he has a peculiar pattern, albeit he is quite aggressive and the breeder, Mr. Lincoln, advised him against the move…Mr. Lincoln is African American and Birdy is worried that the mother (and father for this instance) might find about the color of his skin and then there would be major trouble, which proves again what a vile person the woman is, and with this evidence, we might say that about the father, even if these were other times and being a racist seems to have been the norm, especially on some latitudes in America, where the cult of Trump dominates today<br />Birdy is gullible and lives in another universe, he wants to be a bird, is happiest in their company…Alfonso Columbato has a project in school, he has to write about an event and he thinks of creating one with the help of his friend…so he has this idea of pretending to have the map of a treasure, he takes the trouble to use fire to make the paper look old and then he pretends to Birdy that he has found the genuine article and thus they go on a treasure hunt about which Al will write later, at least that is the plan…<br />Birdy embarks on the hunt with all his energy and astonishingly, even when Al tells him, after a nasty rain and a lot of digging that it was all a hoax for the school project, birdy acts as if the treasure is real and only waits for them to find it and keeps digging after his friend will have left…the following day, Alfonso wonders how was it possible for his friend to get out from the incredible hole, grave like that was there…<br /></span>
