  <span id="freeText2932365376036181152" style="display:none">It is quite a short book but I read it for about 2 weeks. I have to admit that it is not an easy and pleasant to read. The book tells the story of life of 2 boys, then adult men. One of them, the title Birdy, ended up in a psychiatric hospital. He is visited by his friend Al, who tells him about their childhood adventures. All his life he was even obsessed with birds and flying. The book is very symbolic at the same time the author speaks about many things very bluntly. He does not avoid disgusting, disturbing descriptions that shock and even disgust the reader. I admit that most of the time the reader had no idea what the book leads to only after reading the ending, everything made sense to me, so don't be discouraged.The only problem I had with this story were long and very detailed descriptions of birds and their behaviour which were quite tiring. To sum up, 'Birdy' is a story about dreams, the meaning of life, freedom, and it stays with us for a long time after reading it, but not everyone will be able to see it.The only problem I had with this story were long and very detailed descriptions of birds and their behaviour which were quite tiring. To sum up, 'Bird' is a story about dreams, the meaning of life, freedom, and it stays with us for a long time after reading it, but not everyone will like it because it is full of truly turpistic descriptions.</span>
