  <span id="freeText3660234339997208747" style="display:none">I saw the movie based on this book way back in 1984. I was a huge fan of the music Peter Gabriel wrote for the soundtrack. I liked the story too. I've finally read the book and it's a really excellent experience. It's made me think deeply about many things, one of the halmarks of an all time classic. I think the characters are well conceived. I came away with a very clear picture of both main characters. It was fun to hear about places around Philadelphia, since I live near there. I liked the intense observations of birds. I wonder how much of it is true or part of the imagination of Birdy. It all seems very believable. The ending left me a little confused at first, but when I understood it, I was sort of left without the kind of resolution the movie gives you. Perhaps it really isn't necessary. The two main characters got to another stage in their relationship and that is enough. I thoroughly enjoyed it. It'll be one of my favorite reads for a long time, I think. </span>
